description:
Retroactive tightening of fz-duq.2's three repro unit tests.
Independent of fz-qbg.1/.2/.3 — can ship at any time.

## Motivation

fz-duq.2's three repro unit tests (`lower_if_*_no_panic` etc.) assert
IR shape (`s.contains("tail_call")`) rather than runtime correctness.
The end-to-end stdout verification lives in the fixture matrix from
fz-duq.5 — two commits later in the DAG. If someone bisects to .2
and the test goes green, they're trusting the test name more than
the assertions.

This ticket adds a test-only helper that compiles + runs a fz program
through the JIT and captures its stdout, then rewrites the three
tests to assert stdout equality.

## Add helper

In `src/ir_lower.rs::tests`:

```rust
fn run_and_capture(src: &str) -> String {
    use crate::fz_ir::Module;
    use crate::ir_codegen::compile;
    let m: Module = lower_src(src);
    let entry = m.fn_by_name("main").expect("no main fn").id;
    let _ = fz_runtime::ir_runtime::test_capture_take();
    let _ = compile(&m).unwrap().run(entry);
    fz_runtime::ir_runtime::test_capture_take().join("\n")
}
```

(Pattern matches existing `capture_main` in `src/ir_codegen.rs:6859`.)

## Replace three weak tests

```rust
#[test]
fn fz_84m_repro_a_prints_99() {
    let out = run_and_capture(
        "fn helper(), do: 7\n\
         fn main() do\n\
           if 1 == 0 do print(helper()) else print(99) end\n\
         end",
    );
    assert_eq!(out, "99");
}

#[test]
fn fz_84m_repro_b_prints_7_then_99() {
    let out = run_and_capture(
        "fn helper(), do: 7\n\
         fn pick(n) do if n == 0 do helper() else 99 end end\n\
         fn main() do print(pick(0)); print(pick(1)) end",
    );
    assert_eq!(out, "7\n99");
}

#[test]
fn fz_84m_repro_c_prints_7_then_99_no_narrowing() {
    let out = run_and_capture(
        "fn helper(), do: 7\n\
         fn pick(n) do if n > 0 do helper() else 99 end end\n\
         fn main() do print(pick(5)); print(pick(0)) end",
    );
    assert_eq!(out, "7\n99");
}
```

## What's removed

- `src/ir_lower.rs::tests::lower_if_constant_cond_with_call_in_arm_no_panic`
- `src/ir_lower.rs::tests::lower_if_tail_call_in_arm_preserved`
- `src/ir_lower.rs::tests::lower_if_unnarrowed_cond_with_tail_call_in_arm`

All three assert IR shape; replaced with end-to-end stdout tests.

## Acceptance

- Three new tests pass.
- Three old tests deleted.
- `cargo test --workspace` green.

## Out of scope

Fixture matrix tests in fz-duq.5 stay — they cover interp/jit/repl/
aot path parity, which the in-process helper doesn't.
